sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Claude (AI Client)
    participant S as MCP Server
    participant I as Yahoo IMAP

    Note over C,S: Session Startup

    C->>S: health_check
    S->>I: Connect + INBOX access
    S-->>C: { healthy: true, checks: {...} }

    C->>S: get_actions
    S-->>C: { actions: [...], total: 23 }

    C->>S: ensure_folders
    S->>I: Create missing folders
    S-->>C: { created: [...], present: [...] }

    Note over C,S: Alert Cleanup (sweep stale alerts)

    C->>S: list_folder_emails("Alerts", before: 3d ago)
    S->>I: SEARCH Alerts folder
    S-->>C: [{ uid, subject, ... }, ...]

    loop Batch delete (chunks of 20)
        C->>S: apply_action("delete", uids[], "Alerts")
        S->>I: Move to for-delete, mark read
        S-->>C: { applied: N }
    end

    Note over C,S: TTL Expiry Sweep

    C->>S: process_ttl_expirations
    S->>S: Load TTL records (expires_at <= now)
    S->>I: Check UIDs still in INBOX
    S->>I: Unflag + move expired to action folders
    S->>S: Prune TTL records
    S-->>C: { checked, moved, orphaned }

    Note over C,S: Main Processing

    C->>S: process_known_senders(date range)
    S->>I: Fetch INBOX in batches of 50
    S->>S: Lookup each sender (exact → regex)
    S->>I: Apply actions for known senders
    S->>S: Hold important emails (create TTL records)
    S-->>C: { known_processed, important_held, unknown_senders[] }
